root -l -b -q 'dumpPOEvents.C("FASERMC-PO-Run500-0_120500.root",5,true,"numuCC,nueCC")' | head -n 80


Usage examples:

Dump first 8 numuCC events:
root -l -b -q 'dumpPOEvents.C("FASERMC-PO-Run500-0_120500.root",8,true,"numuCC")'

Dump up to 5 nueCC or numuCC (summary only, no particle list):
root -l -b -q 'dumpPOEvents.C("FASERMC-PO-Run500-0_120500.root",5,false,"nueCC,numuCC")'

Dump 10 events of any type (no filter):
root -l -b -q 'dumpPOEvents.C("FASERMC-PO-Run500-0_120500.root",10,true,"")'

Filter tokens accepted are the strings returned by reaction_desc():
nueCC, numuCC, nutauCC, antinueCC, antinumuCC, antinutauCC, nuNC, nuES.


root -l -b -q 'plotPO.C("FASERMC-PO-Run500-0_120500.root")'
getting the following
POEventNuE.pdf
POEventSummary.pdf
POEventSummary.root
POEventVertex.pdf




